description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and enthusiastic Band 6 Registered Nurse to join our Pulmonary Outreach Team for COPD (PORT) at Wrexham Maelor hospital. Our respiratory teams are passionate about ensuring that the highest possible standard of care is available to each and every one of its service users. The successful candidate will work alongside our wider respiratory multidisciplinary team to support our aspiration of excellence in all aspects of respiratory care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from enthusiastic and conscientious nursing colleagues who have a particular interest in caring for patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will use your determination and compassion to provide holistic assessments and management plans for patients during their journey from acute hospital admission, to early supported or supported discharge within the patient’s own home. The successful applicant will also provide excellence in care for the wider respiratory patient group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pam Lloyd - Lead Respiratory Nurse Specialist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pam.Lloyd@Wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;03000 858457&lt;/p&gt;
